======================================================================
  FAIRNESS ANALYSIS: Sirius Data-on-CPU
======================================================================
  For each query in a FRESH DuckDB process:
    - gpu_buffer_init() allocates GPU memory (constant cost)
    - 1st gpu_processing() = transfers data from CPU → GPU + computes
    - 2nd+ gpu_processing() = data already on GPU, just computes

  Fair measurement approach:
    - Data-on-CPU cost = first_run_s (includes buffer init + transfer + compute)
    - Data-on-GPU cost = min_subsequent_s (just compute, data cached)
    - Transfer overhead = first_run_s - min_subsequent_s

